Greek fire chief Christos Smetis confirmed the tragic loss of all 121 individuals aboard the Helios Airways flight that crashed in Greece.
Reports indicated a history of decompression issues with the plane, sparking anger among relatives.
Concerns arose over a potential technical fault affecting similar Helios jets.
Aviation experts speculated on the crew's response to a possible lack of oxygen, highlighting the critical moments before the crash.
The recovery of black boxes and ongoing investigations aimed to uncover the cause of the devastating incident, ruling out terrorism as a factor.
The European Union Transport Commissioner expressed condolences and emphasized the need for enhanced safety measures in air travel.
